main() also has its own local static variable named ‘a' that hides the global ‘a' in main. The printf() statement in main() accesses the local ‘a' and prints its value. The same printf() statement accesses the global ‘b' as there is no local variable named ‘b' in main. Also, the defaut value of static and global int variables is 0. That is why the printf statement in main() prints 0 as value of b.</div></div></div><div class="mtq_question mtq_scroll_item-1" id="mtq_question-14-1"><table class="mtq_question_heading_table"><tr><td><div class="mtq_question_label ">Question 14</div><div id="mtq_stamp-14-1" class="mtq_stamp"></div></td></tr></table><div id="mtq_question_text-14-1" class="mtq_question_text">What output will be generated by the given code d\segment if:
